exchanges.description:
Formaldehyde is an organic chemical, which is a colorless gas at ambient temperature that has a pungent, suffocating odor and polymerizes in the presence of acids or alkali agents. Formaldehyde is used for the production of:
- a large variety of resins generated through reaction with other compounds such as phenol or urea. These resins are used as adhesives, bonding agents, glues, paints, coating and other applications;
- MDI (methyl diisocyanate), for polyurethanes;
- polyoxymethylene, a formaldehyde polymer used as an engineering plastic;
- polyols for water-soluble paints and coatings;
- hydraulic fluids and lubricants, etc.
